Task: Code Review Fixes — avatars.js GPU/DOM Memory Leaks (7 fixes)

SUMMARY:
Applied all 7 code-review fixes to /Users/dbroggy/CODE/Cyber_Back_to_School/js/avatars.js to eliminate GPU memory leaks, DOM event listener accumulation, and redundant observer creation.

FIXES APPLIED:

Fix 1 (Critical): Geometry and material disposal in every builder.
- Added _disposables[] array in all 5 builders.
- Replaced inline mat() arrow with a tracking version that pushes every MeshStandardMaterial to _disposables.
- Pushed every geometry to _disposables immediately after construction.
- Each builder now returns dispose: () => { _disposables.forEach(d => d.dispose()); }.
- disposeAvatars() calls entry.dispose() before entry.renderer.dispose().

Fix 2 (Critical): Eliminated hover event listener accumulation.
- Each canvas entry now gets its own AbortController (hoverController).
- mouseenter/mouseleave listeners are registered with { signal: hoverController.signal }.
- disposeAvatars() calls entry._abortController.abort(), automatically removing both listeners.

Fix 3 (Important): Consolidated to one IntersectionObserver.
- Removed per-canvas IntersectionObserver creation from inside the forEach loop.
- After the loop, one shared observer watches #persona-section and pauses/resumes all renderers.
- Each _avatarRenderers entry stores animateFn alongside renderer, dispose, and _abortController.

Fix 4 (Important): Fixed Explorer builder add-then-remove pattern.
- Group created FIRST; all meshes added directly to the group.
- Eliminated the scene.add/scene.remove/group.add shuffle.

Fix 5 (Important): Removed unused pointLight destructure in initAvatars().
- Changed destructuring assignment to const built = builder(canvas); fields accessed via built.*.

Fix 6 (Important): Shared rivet geometry in buildBuilderAvatar.
- Single rivetGeo declared before the rivetPositions.forEach loop; reused for all 6 rivets.

Fix 7 (Suggestion): Double-init guard in initAvatars().
- if (_avatarRenderers.length > 0) disposeAvatars() added at top of initAvatars().

