Date: 2026-03-19
Task: Code Review — Task 7 Explorer Hub (Plan 2: Dark Mode, Avatars, Explorer Hub)
SHAs reviewed: base=40fd548 head=511a363

REVIEW OUTCOME: PASS WITH IMPORTANT NOTES

Plan alignment: FULL. All 10 verification checklist items from the plan are implementable
from the delivered code. No features were skipped or incorrectly deviated from.

Issues found (4 total — 0 Critical, 2 Important, 2 Suggestions):

IMPORTANT 1: Double markPageVisited() call
- xp.js DOMContentLoaded auto-handler (line 275-279 of xp.js) calls markPageVisited()
  with the current page filename automatically on every page.
- explorer.html DOMContentLoaded also calls markPageVisited('explorer.html') explicitly.
- markPageVisited() is idempotent (guards with visited.includes()), so XP is not
  double-awarded. However the explicit call is redundant and causes confusion.
- Recommendation: remove the explicit markPageVisited call from explorer.html's
  DOMContentLoaded, since xp.js already handles it universally.

IMPORTANT 2: No ARIA attributes on expand/collapse buttons
- career-expand-btn elements have no aria-expanded attribute and the controlled
  career-details div has no aria-labelledby or id linkage for screen readers.
- Recommendation: add aria-expanded="false"/"true" to each button toggled in
  _expandCareer(), and aria-controls="details-${c.id}" on the button element.

SUGGESTION 1: Inline styles should move to CSS classes
- Multiple elements use inline style="" on HTML elements and in template literals
  (font-size, color, margin-bottom, font-family etc.). This conflicts with the
  established pattern of CSS classes for all visual styling.
- No functional issue, but reduces maintainability and light-mode override capability.

SUGGESTION 2: _addPageXP() does not reset the hero counter on page reload
- pageXpEarned is initialized to 0 on every page load. If a returning student has
  already earned XP from this page in a prior session, the counter correctly shows 0
  (they will earn no more XP). This is the intended behavior per the plan. No bug.
  Document this design decision with a comment for future maintainers.

Author: David Broggy

